M|subagent-driven-development|Use the least powerful model that can handle each role to conserve cost and increase speed.
M|subagent-driven-development|**Mechanical implementation tasks** (isolated functions, clear specs, 1-2 files): use a fast, cheap model. Most implementation tasks are mechanical when the plan is well-specified.
M|subagent-driven-development|**Integration and judgment tasks** (multi-file coordination, pattern matching, debugging): use a standard model.
M|subagent-driven-development|**Architecture, design, and rv tasks**: use the most capable available model.
M|subagent-driven-development|**Task complexity signals:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- Touches 1-2 files with a complete spec → cheap model
M|subagent-driven-development|- Touches multiple files with integration concerns → standard model
M|subagent-driven-development|- Requires design judgment or broad codebase understanding → most capable model
M|subagent-driven-development|Implementer subagents report one of four statuses. Handle each appropriately:
M|subagent-driven-development|**DONE:** Proceed to spec compliance rv.
M|subagent-driven-development|**DONE_WITH_CONCERNS:** The implementer completed the work but flagged doubts. Read the concerns before proceeding. If the concerns are about correctness or scope, address them before rv. If they're o
M|subagent-driven-development|**NEEDS_CONTEXT:** The implementer needs information that wasn't provided. Provide the missing ctx and re-dispatch.
M|subagent-driven-development|**BLOCKED:** The implementer cannot complete the task. Assess the blocker:
M|subagent-driven-development|1. If it's a ctx problem, provide more ctx and re-dispatch with the same model
M|subagent-driven-development|2. If the task requires more reasoning, re-dispatch with a more capable model
M|subagent-driven-development|3. If the task is too large, break it into smaller pieces
M|subagent-driven-development|4. If the plan itself is wrong, escalate to the human
M|subagent-driven-development|**Never** ignore an escalation or force the same model to retry without changes. If the implementer said it's stuck, something needs to change.
M|subagent-driven-development|- `./implementer-prompt.md` - Dispatch implementer subagent
M|subagent-driven-development|- `./spec-reviewer-prompt.md` - Dispatch spec compliance reviewer subagent
M|subagent-driven-development|- `./code-quality-reviewer-prompt.md` - Dispatch code quality reviewer subagent
M|subagent-driven-development|```
