M|subagent-driven-development|**vs. Manual execution:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- Subagents follow TDD naturally
M|subagent-driven-development|- Fresh ctx per task (no confusion)
M|subagent-driven-development|- Parallel-safe (subagents don't interfere)
M|subagent-driven-development|- Subagent can ask questions (before AND during work)
M|subagent-driven-development|**vs. Executing Plans:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- Same ses (no handoff)
M|subagent-driven-development|- Continuous progress (no waiting)
M|subagent-driven-development|- rv checkpoints automatic
M|subagent-driven-development|**Efficiency gains:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- No file reading overhead (controller provides full text)
M|subagent-driven-development|- Controller curates exactly what ctx is needed
M|subagent-driven-development|- Subagent gets complete information upfront
M|subagent-driven-development|- Questions surfaced before work begins (not after)
M|subagent-driven-development|**Quality gates:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- Self-rv catches issues before handoff
M|subagent-driven-development|- Two-stage rv: spec compliance, then code quality
M|subagent-driven-development|- rv loops ensure fixes actually work
M|subagent-driven-development|- Spec compliance prevents over/under-building
M|subagent-driven-development|- Code quality ensures implementation is well-built
M|subagent-driven-development|**Cost:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- More subagent invocations (implementer + 2 reviewers per task)
M|subagent-driven-development|- Controller does more prep work (extracting all tasks upfront)
M|subagent-driven-development|- rv loops add iterations
M|subagent-driven-development|- But catches issues early (cheaper than debugging later)
M|subagent-driven-development|**Never:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- Start implementation on main/master branch without explicit user consent
M|subagent-driven-development|- Skip reviews (spec compliance OR code quality)
M|subagent-driven-development|- Proceed with unfixed issues
M|subagent-driven-development|- Dispatch multiple implementation subagents in parallel (conflicts)
M|subagent-driven-development|- Make subagent read plan file (provide full text instead)
M|subagent-driven-development|- Skip scene-setting ctx (subagent needs to understand where task fits)
M|subagent-driven-development|- Ignore subagent questions (answer before letting them proceed)
M|subagent-driven-development|- Accept "close enough" on spec compliance (spec reviewer found issues = not done)
M|subagent-driven-development|- Skip rv loops (reviewer found issues = implementer fixes = rv again)
M|subagent-driven-development|- Let implementer self-rv replace actual rv (both are needed)
M|subagent-driven-development|- **Start code quality rv before spec compliance is ✅** (wrong order)
M|subagent-driven-development|- Move to next task while either rv has open issues
M|subagent-driven-development|**If subagent asks questions:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- Answer clearly and completely
M|subagent-driven-development|- Provide additional ctx if needed
M|subagent-driven-development|- Don't rush them into implementation
M|subagent-driven-development|**If reviewer finds issues:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- Implementer (same subagent) fixes them
M|subagent-driven-development|- Reviewer reviews again
M|subagent-driven-development|- Repeat until ap
M|subagent-driven-development|- Don't skip the re-rv
M|subagent-driven-development|**If subagent fails task:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- Dispatch fix subagent with specific instructions
M|subagent-driven-development|- Don't try to fix manually (ctx pollution)
M|subagent-driven-development|**Required workflow skills:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- **superpowers:using-git-worktrees** - REQUIRED: Set up isolated workspace before starting
M|subagent-driven-development|- **superpowers:writing-plans** - Creates the plan this skill executes
M|subagent-driven-development|- **superpowers:requesting-code-rv** - Code rv template for reviewer subagents
M|subagent-driven-development|- **superpowers:finishing-a-dev-branch** - Complete dev after all tasks
M|subagent-driven-development|**Subagents should use:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- **superpowers:test-driven-dev** - Subagents follow TDD for each task
M|subagent-driven-development|**Alternative workflow:**
M|subagent-driven-development|- **superpowers:executing-plans** - Use for parallel ses instead of same-ses execution